<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><title>Angi Pro lead-gen math</title></head>
<body style="margin:0;padding:0;background-color:#ffffff;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;color:#27272a;">
  <div style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;padding:32px 20px;">
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Hey,</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Last email. The Angi Pro pitch, written so you can evaluate it instead of being sold to.</p>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">What to understand</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 10px 0;">Angi Pro is a lead channel. Homeowners submit project requests, and participating pros can receive leads that match their trade and service area. You still have to respond, qualify, sell, and win the job.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">The math is simple: lead cost divided by close rate equals cost per won job. Compare that against gross profit on the job type you want more of.</p>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">When it can make sense</h2>
    <ul style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;margin:0 0 18px 24px;padding:0;">
      <li>You have unused capacity and incremental jobs would turn into revenue.</li>
      <li>You are entering a new service area and need job volume faster than referrals can build it.</li>
      <li>You want more of a specific project type and can respond quickly.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">When to skip it</h2>
    <ul style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;margin:0 0 18px 24px;padding:0;">
      <li>You are already booked out and should raise prices before buying demand.</li>
      <li>You cannot respond quickly to new inquiries.</li>
      <li>Your close rate or average job profit cannot absorb paid-lead costs.</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 24px 0;"><a href="{{ cta_url }}" style="color:#FF6B2B;font-weight:600;text-decoration:underline;">Sign up as an Angi Pro</a></p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">That is the sequence. The tools stay free whether or not Angi Pro makes sense for your shop.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:20px 0 4px 0;">&mdash; NailTheQuote</p>
